<seg id="1">Arrest made in shooting death of LSU's Sims</seg>
<seg id="2">Police in Baton Rouge, La., announced Saturday that a suspect has been arrested in the shooting death of LSU basketball player Wayde Sims on Friday.</seg>
<seg id="3">The Baton Rouge Police Department announced the arrest of Dyteon Simpson, 20, at an 11 a.m. ET news conference.</seg>
<seg id="4">They had released a video of the shooting on Friday, asking for help identifying a man seen in the footage.</seg>
<seg id="5">Sims, 20, was shot and killed near Southern University's campus early Friday.</seg>
<seg id="6">"Wayde Sims suffered a gunshot wound to the head and ultimately died as a result," police chief Murphy J. Paul told the media Saturday, per 247sports.</seg>
<seg id="7">Wayde stepped in to defend his friend and was shot by Simpson.</seg>
<seg id="8">Simpson was questioned and admitted to being on scene, in possession of a weapon, and admitted to shooting Wayde Sims.</seg>
<seg id="9">Simpson was arrested without incident and taken into custody at East Baton Rouge Parish Police Department.</seg>
<seg id="10">A 6-foot-6 junior who grew up in Baton Rouge, Sims played in 32 games with 10 starts last season and averaged 17.4 minutes, 5.6 points and 2.9 rebounds per game.</seg>
